    "recap_headline": "University of Toledo",
    "recap_text": "TOLEDO, Ohio \u2013 The Toledo baseball team erupted for seven runs in the eighth inning and the pitching staff displayed a dominant effort on the mound in a 10-1 victory over Central Michigan at Keilitz Field on Friday.\nThe Rockets (10-9, 6-1 MAC) got in front with two runs in the first, and held that 2-0 edge throughout the first six innings. Up 2-1 entering the eighth, Toledo scored seven runs with two outs to break the game open. Toledo has won seven of its last eight overall and is 5-1 in series openers this season.\nJuniors\nCole Cahill\nand\nCharlie Scholvin\neach produced three hits while redshirt juniors\nTroy Sudbrook\nand\nLuke Walton\nand redshirt freshman\nRyan Sudbrook\neach added two hits. Cahill had a career-high five RBIs, including a grand slam in the eighth inning.\nOn the mound,\nNathan Leininger\n(4-0) got another win, pitching a career-high eight innings, and not allowing a run until the seventh. He allowed just five hits and struck out 10 batters without allowing a walk.\nMichael Fliss\nfinished off the game in the ninth.\nToledo looks for the series victory tomorrow, with first pitch at 1:00 p.m.\nQuoting Head Coach\nRob Reinstetle\n\"That is a big win on a Friday night in the MAC. Their guy came in having thrown the ball well all year. Our offense executed the game plan and got us off to a great start. Nate Leininger was fantastic again and kept us in the game, allowing us to blow it open late. Really proud of the boys. Need to do it again tomorrow and win the series.\"\nTop Rocket Hitters\nCole Cahill\n\u2013 3-for-4, HR (1), 5 RBIs, 1 run, 1 2B, 1 BB\nCharlie Scholvin\n\u2013 3-for-6, 3 RBIs, 2 runs, 2 2B\nTroy Sudbrook\n\u2013 2-for-5, 2 RBIs, 2 runs\nLuke Walton\n\u2013 2-for-5, 1 run\nRyan Sudbrook\n\u2013 2-for-3, 1 2B\nPitching Lines\nNathan Leininger\n(W, 4-0) \u2013 8.0 IP, 5 H, 1 R, 0 BB, 10 Ks\nMichael Fliss\n\u2013 1.0 IP, 0 H, 0 R, 0 BB, 2 Ks\nHow it Happened\nTroy Sudbrook's\nRBI single and\nCole Cahill's\nRBI double gave Toledo a 2-0 lead in the first.\nThe Chippewas got on the board in the bottom of the seventh on an RBI single to cut the lead to 2-1.\nWith two outs in the eighth inning,\nCharlie Scholvin\nproduced a two-run double, followed by another RBI single from Sudbrook. Then, Toledo loaded the bases, setting up\nCole Cahill's\ngrand slam for a seven-run inning and a 9-1 lead.\nScholvin added another RBI in the ninth on a single.",
